1. Napolju je *mraz* danas. (It's freezing outside today.)
2. Moramo da stavimo namirnice u frižider da ne bi bile izložene *mrazu*. (We need to put the groceries in the fridge so they won't be exposed to the cold.)
3. Osećam *mraz* u kostima kada je vreme ovako hladno. (I feel the cold in my bones when the weather is this cold.)
4. Sinoć je *mraz* bio veoma jak, led se stvorio na prozorima. (Last night, the frost was very strong, ice formed on the windows.)
5. Voda u cevima će se smrznuti ako ne zaštitite kuću od *mraza*. (The water in the pipes will freeze if you don't protect the house from the frost.)
6. On je okrenuo *mrzovoljno* glavu kada sam ga pozdravila. (He turned his head *gloomily* when I greeted him.)
7. Kada sam čula tu vest, osetila sam *mržnju* prema tom čoveku. (When I heard that news, I felt *hatred* towards that man.)
8. Njegov *mrzak* pogled me je uplašio. (His *cold* gaze scared me.)
9. Njena *mrzovolja* je bila primetna kada je ušla u sobu. (Her *surliness* was noticeable when she entered the room.)
10. *Mrazno* jutro me je dočekalo kada sam izašao napolje. (A *frosty* morning greeted me when I went outside.)